## 🗺 NAVIGATION SYSTEM
The navigation is role-driven and complex. DO NOT modify nav config without reading:
- `shared/clientNav.ts` (31K lines — the full nav definition)
- `shared/roleNavConfig.ts` — which nav items are visible per role
- `shared/hubNavVisibility.ts` — hub-level visibility rules
- `shared/navPlatformRestrictedPrefixes.ts` — platform-only paths

To add a new page to nav:
1. Add the page component to `client/src/pages/`
2. Add a route in `client/src/App.tsx`  
3. Add nav entry in `shared/clientNav.ts` with correct `roles` array
4. Test with `shared/roleNavConfig.test.ts`

